=== Gate 15: Manual Trackpad Input Capture ===
Initial attempt: Sun Jul 19 2026
Second physical retest and revised evaluation: Tue Jul 21 2026
Final verdict: PASS — Adam's revised physical acceptance

Adam's first physical attempt (2026-07-19) failed honestly:
  - Pinch worked, but same-direction two-finger movement also zoomed.
  - Input-log mode did not visibly re-render during capture.

The 2026-07-20 fix made wheel/scroll pan, made raw finger motion pan-only,
reserved zoom for SDL_EVENT_PINCH_UPDATE, and re-rendered input-log mode.

Adam's second macOS physical capture (2026-07-21) reported:
  totalEvents: 512
  scrollEventCount: 488
  fingerEventCount: 0
  hasNonzeroViewportResponse: true
  hasAppliedPanOutcome: true
  hasAppliedPinchOutcome: true
  droppedOrInvalid: 0

Adam's physical observation:
  - Two fingers panned horizontally and vertically without unwanted zoom.
  - Pinch zoom worked.
  - Three-finger behaviour was tried, did nothing, and is not required.

Revised acceptance (Adam's explicit waiver, 2026-07-21):
  SDL/macOS may report correct two-finger trackpad pan/pinch through scroll and
  pinch streams without SDL_EVENT_FINGER_* records. fingerEventCount remains
  measured and reported diagnostic telemetry, but has no required minimum.
  The meaningful requirements are robust event volume (>=50 total, >=30
  scroll), subpixel deltas, zero invalid/dropped records, nonzero viewport
  response, an applied pan outcome, and an applied pinch outcome, plus the
  existing duration/rate/timestamp/gesture validity criteria. The capture above
  satisfies the revised criteria and is PASS. No fake finger count was added.

Saved-file re-evaluation:
  The input-log executable records a live session but has no CSV re-evaluation
  mode, so it cannot regenerate a summary for an existing CSV after the fact.
  At this review, /tmp/trackpad_capture.csv.summary.txt is retained as a
  separate older summary with 369 total events, 315 scroll events, 0 finger
  events, 18.820916 s duration, 70.000 Hz peak rate, monotonic timestamps,
  subpixel deltas, zero invalid records, and true viewport/pan/pinch outcomes.
  Its recorded FAIL is solely the former finger threshold. Under the revised
  rule those factual metrics also pass. The Adam-reported 512/488 capture above
  is the physical gate record for this evidence item; the local CSV differs and
  is not relabelled or altered as if it were that capture.

Future capture command:
  cd spikes/m0/rendering-accessibility/build
  ./m0_spike --input-log --input-log-path /tmp/trackpad_capture.csv \
      --input-device trackpad \
      --bravura-font bravura_font/Bravura.otf \
      --text-font noto_font/NotoSans-Regular.ttf

Required physical actions:
  1. Two-finger pan horizontally and vertically; it must not zoom.
  2. Pinch zoom; it must apply a scale change.
  3. Close with Escape.
